Experiment No: 1		      		 					 Date: 

POWER OF THE SIGNAL
PROGRAM

clc;
clear all;
close all;
N=2;
x=ones(1,N);
for i=1:N;
    y(i)=(1/3)^i.*x(i);
end;
n=N;
e=0;
for i=1:n;
    e=e+(y(i).*y(i));
end;
p=e/(2*N+1);
disp('The power of the signal is');
disp(p);
COMMAND WINDOW
The power of the signal is
    0.0247
POWER FOR PERIODIC SIGNAL
PROGRAM
clc;
clear all;
close all;
N=input('Type the value of N');
t= -N:0.00001:N;
x=cos(2*pi*50*t).^2;
disp('The calculated power of the signal is');
p=sum((abs(x).^2)/length(x));
disp(p);
plot(t,x);
axis([0 0.1 0 1]);
COMMAND WINDOW
Type the value of N 5
The calculated power of the signal is
    0.3750

